  "prompt": "What are some karaoke songs for a 2nd alto?",
  "response": "Here are some great karaoke song suggestions for a 2nd alto voice, which typically sits in the lower range of female vocals. These songs often have melodies that are more accessible for a 2nd alto:\n\n1. **\"Landslide\" by Fleetwood Mac**\n2. **\"Someone Like You\" by Adele**\n3. **\"Back to Black\" by Amy Winehouse**\n4. **\"Royals\" by Lorde**\n5. **\"Dreams\" by Fleetwood Mac**\n6. **\"Killing Me Softly\" by Roberta Flack or The Fugees**\n7. **\"Someone You Loved\" by Lewis Capaldi**\n8. **\"Waiting on the World to Change\" by John Mayer**\n9. **\"If I Ain't Got You\" by Alicia Keys**\n10. **\"Make You Feel My Love\" by Bob Dylan (or covered by Adele)**\n11. **\"Brass in Pocket\" by The Pretenders**\n12. **\"Stay\" by Rihanna (featuring Mikky Ekko)**\n13. **\"Have I Told You Lately\" by Rod Stewart**\n14. **\"Yesterday\" by The Beatles**\n15. **\"I Will Always Love You\" by Dolly Parton (a lower key version)**\n\nFeel free to adjust the key of any song to better fit your vocal range! Enjoy your karaoke night!",
